The paper deals with the formalism of constraint handling rules, which is a well-known technique in artificial intelligence for solving constraint satisfaction problems. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely category. The paper also deals with logic and quantification, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the models, which could place it in cs.PL (Programming Languages) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper deals with the solving of games, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
